; advapi32.def
;
; Minimal .def for privilege/token/security functions. All
; three exports here are stubbed as "return success, do
; nothing" in v0 — a running process on DuetOS has no real
; security model (no user accounts, no ACLs, no token
; granularity), so pretending to succeed is both honest and
; safe. Programs that check the BOOL return to gate real
; effects (e.g. enabling SeDebugPrivilege to read other
; process memory) will continue their setup dance and never
; actually exercise the privileged code path.
;
; Keep in sync with kernel/subsystems/win32/stubs.cpp entries
; under LIBRARY advapi32.dll.

LIBRARY advapi32.dll

EXPORTS
    OpenProcessToken
    LookupPrivilegeValueW
    LookupPrivilegeValueA
    AdjustTokenPrivileges
    ; Batch 34 — identity queries
    GetUserNameW
    ; Batch 37 — registry no-op stubs
    RegOpenKeyExW
    RegQueryValueExW
    RegCloseKey
